headline: FedEx Predicts $1 Billion Tariffs Hit to Fiscal 2026 Earnings
summary: Parcel giant FedEx said it expects a $1 billion hit to its earnings this fiscal year because of changes in the global trade environment stemming from U.S. tariffs.  In the prior fiscal year ended in May, FedEx reported $6.1 billion in adjusted operating income.  FedEx reduced its Trans-Pacific Asia outbound capacity by 25% year-over-year in the quarter ended in August, and by 10% from the prior quarter.

headline: FedEx results top targets on cost-cutting, shares jump 5.5% after the bell
summary: FedEx reported quarterly profit and revenue above Wall Street estimates, as cost-cutting and strength in domestic deliveries helped offset weaker international volumes after the U.S. ended tariff exemptions on low-value, direct-to-consumer shipments.  Shares of Memphis-based FedEx climbed 5.5% in extended trading on Thursday after surprising Wall Street.  Analysts had expected profit per share to fall due to the end of "de minimis" exemptions, which allowed shipments valued under $800 to enter the U.S. duty-free.
